.TH "MERGELOG\-RS" "1" "2026\-03\-24" ""
.SH mergelog\-rs
Merge and sort HTTP log files chronologically \(em Rust rewrite of \c
.UR https://mergelog.sourceforge.net/
mergelog 4.5
.UE \c
\ by Bertrand Demiddelaer.
.SS Synopsis
.IP
.EX
mergelog\-rs [OPTIONS] <FILE>...
.EE
.SS Description
\f[CR]mergelog\-rs\f[R] reads multiple HTTP log files and writes a
single chronologically sorted stream to stdout (or a file).
It is designed for consolidating logs from multiple servers behind a
round\-robin DNS.
.PP
Supported input formats: \f[B]NCSA Combined Log Format\f[R] (CLF) and
\f[B]Caddy JSON\f[R] access logs.
The format is auto\-detected per file \(em no flag needed for mixed
inputs.
.PP
All input files must be sorted chronologically within themselves (as
Apache, nginx, and Caddy produce them).
Timestamps are compared in UTC \(em timezone offsets in CLF lines are
correctly handled.
.SS Log Formats
.SS CLF \(em NCSA Combined Log Format
.IP
.EX
%h %l %u %t \(dq%r\(dq %>s %b \(dq%{Referer}i\(dq \(dq%{User\-agent}i\(dq
.EE
.PP
Example:
.IP
.EX
93.184.216.34 \- alice [15/Mar/2026:12:00:00 +0100] \(dqGET /index.html HTTP/1.1\(dq 200 4096 \(dqhttps://example.com/\(dq \(dqMozilla/5.0\(dq
.EE
.PP
The timestamp field \f[CR]%t\f[R] uses the format
\f[CR][DD/Mon/YYYY:HH:MM:SS ±HHMM]\f[R].
.PP
Lines whose timestamp cannot be parsed are sorted to the \f[B]end\f[R]
of the output (matching the behaviour of the original mergelog 4.5).
.SS Caddy JSON
Caddy access logs written in JSON format (one object per line):
.IP
.EX
{\(dqts\(dq:\(dq2026\-03\-22T14:50:51.525Z\(dq,\(dqrequest\(dq:{\(dqclient_ip\(dq:\(dq1.2.3.4\(dq,\(dqmethod\(dq:\(dqGET\(dq,\(dquri\(dq:\(dq/\(dq,\(dqproto\(dq:\(dqHTTP/1.1\(dq,\(dqheaders\(dq:{}},\(dqstatus\(dq:200,\(dqsize\(dq:1234,\(dquser_id\(dq:\(dq\(dq}
.EE
.PP
The \f[CR]ts\f[R] field may be an ISO 8601 string
(\f[CR]\(dq2026\-03\-22T14:50:51.525Z\(dq\f[R]) or a Unix float
(\f[CR]1742651451.525\f[R]).
Non\-request lines (error/info/debug entries without a
\f[CR]request\f[R] field) are skipped silently.
Output is always CLF.
