.SS Examples
\f[B]Merge plain\-text CLF log files:\f[R]
.IP
.EX
mergelog\-rs access1.log access2.log access3.log > merged.log
.EE
.PP
\f[B]Merge Caddy JSON logs (auto\-detected, output is CLF):\f[R]
.IP
.EX
mergelog\-rs caddy1.log caddy2.log > merged.log
.EE
.PP
\f[B]Mix CLF and Caddy JSON (auto\-detected per file):\f[R]
.IP
.EX
mergelog\-rs nginx.log caddy.log > merged.log
.EE
.PP
\f[B]Force Caddy format for all files:\f[R]
.IP
.EX
mergelog\-rs \-\-format caddy pod1.log pod2.log > merged.log
.EE
.PP
\f[B]Merge compressed log files (compression auto\-detected):\f[R]
.IP
.EX
mergelog\-rs access.log.gz archive.log.bz2 old.log.xz > merged.log
.EE
.PP
\f[B]Read from stdin (e.g.\ over SSH):\f[R]
.IP
.EX
ssh web01 \(dqcat /var/log/caddy/access.log\(dq \f[B]|\f[R] mergelog\-rs \- /var/log/caddy/access.log
.EE
.PP
\f[B]Write to a file instead of stdout:\f[R]
.IP
.EX
mergelog\-rs \-o merged.log access1.log access2.log
.EE
.PP
\f[B]Show progress and statistics:\f[R]
.IP
.EX
mergelog\-rs \-\-progress \-\-stats access1.log access2.log > merged.log
.EE
.PP
\f[B]Run in a container:\f[R]
.IP
.EX
podman run \-\-rm \-v /var/log/caddy:/logs:ro ghcr.io/git001/mergelog\-rs \(rs
  /logs/access1.log /logs/access2.log > merged.log
.EE
